#inmemory#<meta charset="utf-8"/>
<h3>
 Question 1
</h3>
<co-content>
 <p>
  What does the Processing dist() function do?
 </p>
</co-content>
<form>
 <label>
  <input name="0" type="radio"/>
  <co-content>
   <span>
    It returns the distance between two points
   </span>
  </co-content>
  <br/>
 </label>
 <label>
  <input name="0" type="radio"/>
  <co-content>
   <span>
    It returns the distinction between two objects
   </span>
  </co-content>
  <br/>
 </label>
 <label>
  <input name="0" type="radio"/>
  <co-content>
   <span>
    It distills a variable to a higher accuracy
   </span>
  </co-content>
  <br/>
 </label>
 <label>
  <input name="0" type="radio"/>
  <co-content>
   <span>
    It distorts any given matrix of transformations
   </span>
  </co-content>
  <br/>
 </label>
</form>
<hr/>
<h3>
 Question 2
</h3>
<co-content>
 <p>
  How can we add one to our integer variable currentFrame? Select all that apply.
 </p>
</co-content>
<form>
 <label>
  <input name="1" type="checkbox"/>
  <co-content>
   <span>
    currentFrame  ;
   </span>
  </co-content>
  <br/>
 </label>
 <label>
  <input name="1" type="checkbox"/>
  <co-content>
   <span>
    currentFrame;
   </span>
  </co-content>
  <br/>
 </label>
 <label>
  <input name="1" type="checkbox"/>
  <co-content>
   <span>
    currentFrame = currentFrame   1;
   </span>
  </co-content>
  <br/>
 </label>
 <label>
  <input name="1" type="checkbox"/>
  <co-content>
   <span>
    currentFrame  = 1;
   </span>
  </co-content>
  <br/>
 </label>
</form>
<hr/>
